A chairde,

T=E1 s=FAil agam go bhfuil sibh go maith!

Our 'Seanfhocal' for this week was: 'N=ED thagann ciall roimh aois'
Literal translation =3D Sense does not come before age.
Equivalent to English sayings like "You can't put an old head on young shou=
lders". This is not meant to insult the young by implying that youthfulness=
 always equates to foolishness. Rather, it is a reminder that life=92s most=
 important lessons can only be truly =93learned=94 from experience.

Last night:

  *
We revised the questions on page 49 of the textbook.
  *
We then completed page 50 of the book. Learning 4 of the prepositional pron=
ouns (Forainmneacha R=E9amhfhoclacha)
  *
We watched the following video to help us learn them https://www.studyclix.=
ie/leaving-certificate/irish/higher/grammar/na-reamhfhocail-the-preposition=
s/boost/na-forainmneacha-reamhfhoclacha-le-do-ar-ag-prepositional-pronouns-=
with-tofor-on-at
  *
Pages 51-52 then showed us some examples of these used in sentences and we =
completed Ceacht 11.0
  *
Page 54 was suggested for homework to help revise this work!
  *
We finished up the class by looking at some vocab to do with Pancake Tuesda=
y, here is a list of some of them below!
L=E1 na bPanc=F3ga =3D Pancake Tuesday (Literally translates to 'Day of the=
 pancakes'
Panc=F3g=3D pancake
Panc=F3ga =3D pancakes
Si=FAcra =3D sugar
Pl=FAr =3D flour
Im =3D butter
Bainne =3D milk
Ubh =3D egg
Seacl=E1id =3D chocolate
Liom=F3id =3D lemon
B=E1g=FAn =3D bacon
Mil =3D honey
Friocht=E1n =3D frying pan
Babhla =3D bowl
Sp=FAn=F3g =3D spoon


  *
Please see attached an updated list of class dates for semester 2!
  *
Gaeltacht Trip: Friday 17th- Sunday 19th of April =96 Will be sharing with =
another group. Space for 6/7 from our class- Please let me know by email by=
 tomorrow if you are 100% committed to attending. It'll be first come first=
 served! (Please see attached document for more info).

Go raibh m=EDle maith agaibh.

Le gach dea-ghu=ED,

Laoise Nic =CDomhair

Oifigeach Forbartha Gaeilge, Barr na gCnoc

